      "text": "The further away a balance is from zero, the greater the risk that that account will fail to reciprocate. If no deviation were allowed there would be no liquidity and no trade. If infinite deviation was allowed, some players would only ever give and others only take. We observed earlier that supply always equals demand. Every force has an equal and opposite force. When accounts are hovering around their limits, struggling to reciprocate, that means there is equal and opposite pressure elsewhere in the system."
